          "name": "Digoxin 0.25mg IV",
          "group": "Rate Control",
          "critical": false,
          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Digoxin is not first-line therapy for acute decompensated HF. It has a narrow therapeutic index (toxicity at levels >2 ng/mL), requires careful dosing in renal impairment, and has no proven mortality benefit in HFrEF. Its role is limited to rate control in AF with HF when other agents are contraindicated.",
