          "aiPatientUpdate": "I can talk a little better now. My lips and tongue are still huge but I can breathe. I had no idea my blood pressure medicine could do this.",
          "teaching": "✅ Key teaching: ACE-I angioedema is BRADYKININ-mediated, not histamine. Antihistamines and steroids don't work. Discontinue ACE-I permanently. Avoid ARBs. Document allergy. Switch to amlodipine or other non-RAAS antihypertensive. Observe 24-48h."
