      "Under-resuscitating — 30mL/kg crystalloid bolus (not maintenance rate drip)",
      "Using lactate as a single timepoint rather than trending — repeat at 4-6 hours to assess clearance",
      "Missing the obstructing stone — antibiotics alone will not resolve an obstructed infected system",
      "Not adjusting antibiotics for prior resistance patterns and recent antibiotic exposure",
      "Attributing confusion to 'baseline dementia' without ruling out sepsis in elderly patients"
