          "correct": true,
          "group": "Critical",
          "critical": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Timolol 0.5% ophthalmic drops reduce aqueous humor production by blocking beta-adrenergic receptors in the ciliary body epithelium, lowering IOP within 30 minutes. It is part of the topical IOP-lowering cocktail used alongside pilocarpine and acetazolamide. Systemic absorption can cause bradycardia and bronchospasm — contraindicated in asthma and heart block.",
