          "critical": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Antibiotics alone are uniformly fatal in Fournier's gangrene — this is a surgical emergency requiring radical debridement of all necrotic tissue as the only life-saving intervention. The rapidly spreading infection tracks along fascial planes beyond visible skin changes; antibiotics cannot penetrate the avascular necrotic tissue. Any delay to surgery for optimization or imaging in a stable patient is unacceptable.",
