          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Positioning the ischemic limb in a dependent (below-heart) position uses gravity to maximize hydrostatic perfusion pressure through whatever collateral circulation remains. Elevation is contraindicated as it further reduces arterial inflow pressure. This simple positional maneuver may improve marginal perfusion while awaiting revascularization.",
