      "Concurrent cardiac thrombus (AFib + low EF = high risk of LV mural thrombus — echo indicated)",
      "Phlegmasia cerulea dolens (massive DVT with limb ischemia — different from arterial occlusion but can mimic)",
      "Irreversible ischemia (fixed mottling, muscle rigor, no Doppler signal — amputation, not revascularization)"
