          "teaching": "Acute mesenteric ischemia causes profound third-spacing of fluid into ischemic bowel wall and the peritoneal cavity, plus ongoing hemorrhagic losses. Aggressive IV resuscitation is required to maintain mesenteric perfusion pressure while arranging definitive revascularization. Under-resuscitation worsens gut ischemia in a vicious cycle.",
