          "teaching": "Mannitol 0.5–1 g/kg IV reduces ICP acutely by creating an osmotic gradient that draws water from edematous brain parenchyma into the vasculature. It is a bridge to neurosurgical intervention — it temporizes herniation but does not treat the underlying hematoma. Monitor serum osmolality (target <320 mOsm/kg) and electrolytes during administration.",
