      "PTA is the most common deep space infection of the head and neck — typically follows inadequately treated tonsillitis/pharyngitis",
      "Classic presentation: unilateral sore throat + trismus + 'hot potato' voice + uvular deviation AWAY from the affected side + ipsilateral ear pain",
      "Drainage is the definitive treatment — needle aspiration (can be done bedside, 90%+ success) or incision and drainage. Antibiotics alone are insufficient.",
      "Antibiotic choice: amoxicillin-clavulanate (Augmentin) or ampicillin-sulbactam IV. This patient has C. diff history with clindamycin — avoid clindamycin, use metronidazole if anaerobic coverage needed.",
      "AIRWAY is the #1 concern — assess for stridor, drooling, inability to handle secretions. If airway compromise: do NOT attempt blind intubation (distorted anatomy) — awake fiberoptic or surgical airway.",
