          "teaching": "Ludwig's angina originates from polymicrobial oral flora — streptococcal species, Staphylococcus aureus, and anaerobes from the dental source. High-dose IV penicillin or ampicillin-sulbactam covers most organisms; add metronidazole for enhanced anaerobic coverage. MRSA coverage (vancomycin) is added in immunocompromised patients or those with recent healthcare exposure.",
