          "teaching": "Dexamethasone reduces floor-of-mouth edema and inflammatory induration that causes the characteristic 'woody' hardness of Ludwig's angina. Reducing edema can buy critical time for airway management and may avoid emergency surgical airway. However, steroids are purely temporizing — definitive drainage and dental extraction remain essential.",
