      "Gas gangrene (crepitus on exam or gas on CT — Clostridium infection requires even more emergent debridement)",
      "Lemierre syndrome (IJV thrombosis from pharyngeal infection — check CT for venous thrombosis)",
      "Angioedema (bilateral submandibular swelling without dental source or fever — different etiology, different management)"
