          "group": "Maintenance",
          "critical": false,
          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Hydroxychloroquine (HCQ) must never be stopped during an SLE flare. It reduces flare frequency by 50%, lowers risk of thrombosis, improves long-term survival, and has steroid-sparing effects. Discontinuing HCQ during a flare removes a foundational disease-modifying agent at the worst possible time. It takes months to wash out, so any benefit from stopping is negligible while the harm is immediate.",
