          "critical": true,
          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "All latex-containing materials must be removed from contact with the patient simultaneously with epinephrine administration — gloves, blood pressure cuff bladders, IV tubing stoppers, urinary catheters, tourniquets, and surgical drapes. Switch to nitrile or vinyl alternatives for all ongoing contact. Continued latex exposure during treatment perpetuates mast cell degranulation and prevents recovery.",
