          "name": "Continue with latex gloves",
          "group": "Environmental",
          "critical": false,
          "correct": false,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Continued latex exposure during active anaphylaxis is absolutely contraindicated — ongoing allergen contact perpetuates mast cell degranulation and histamine release, negating the effect of epinephrine and driving refractory or biphasic anaphylaxis. All latex must be removed before any treatment will be fully effective.",
